## I, 22. Charm against jaundice and related diseases.

1\. Up to the sun shall go thy heart-ache and thy jaundice: in the
colour of the red bull do we eovelop thee!  
2. We envelop thee in red tints, unto long life. May this person go
unscathed, and be free of vellow colour!  
3. The cows whose divinity is Rohini, they who, moreover, axe
(themselves) red (róhinin)-(in their) every form and every strength we
do envelop thee.  
4. Into the parrots, into the ropanâkâs (thrush) do we put thy jaundice,
and, furthermore, into the hâridravas (yellow wagtail) do we put thy
jaundice.

